ADB to Provide $97 Million Loan to Pakistan Hydropower Project

-- B y   B a l d a v e   S i n g h
-- 
2011-10-13T02:10:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/adb-to-provide-97-million-loan-to-pakistan-hydropower-project.html
The  Asian Development Bank  will
provide a $97 million loan for the 147-megawatt Patrind
hydropower project in  Pakistan , it said in a website statement.  The run-of-the-river Patrind hydropower plant, between the
Kunhar and Jhelum rivers near Muzaffarabad, is being developed
by Star Hydro Power Ltd., a joint venture between Korea Water
Resources Corp., Daewoo Engineering and Construction Co. and
Sambu Construction Co.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Baldave Singh at 
 bsingh35@bloomberg.net  